==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Naphthalenic
<hw>Naph`tha*len"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to , or derived from, naphthalene; -- used specifically
to designate a yellow crystalline substance, called <xex>naphthalenic
acid</xex> and also <xex>hydroxy quinone</xex>, and obtained from
certain derivatives of naphthol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Naphthalic</ent>⟦br⟧
